Homecoming is the first single from Hey Monday's debut album Hold on Tight. It was first heard on the Fall Out Boy's Welcome To The New Administration Mixtape in August 2008. It was officially released first on October 7, 2008 in the United States.

Hey Monday's first music video is an energetic break-up song. The music video is about lead singer (Pope) and a relationship with a former boyfriend. As she enters she sees a friend of hers and is introduced to her boyfriend, who is Pope's ex-boyfriend. The rest of the music video is mostly flash backs of the times they had together.

Hey Monday is an American Pop Rock band from West Palm Beach, Florida. The band consists of Cassadee Pope (lead vocals), Michael "Jersey" Moriarty (bass guitar), Mike Gentile (lead guitar), Alex Lipshaw (rhythm guitar) and Elliot James (drums.)

Hold on Tight is the debut album of american pop punk band Hey Monday. All the songs featured on the album were co-written by the band. The group has filmed a music video for "Homecoming".The album was produced by: S*A*M (Sam Hollander) and Sluggo, both of whom have worked with many other artists in the past, most notably Gym Class Heroes and The Academy Is.... The band plan to release Homecoming in the UK on 9th March 2009.
